extends LocalDeclarationNode
    LocalVariableNode extension that represents a Parameter of a method. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location, boolean, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ParameterNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                            java.lang.String statement,
                            Location location,
                            boolean require,
                            boolean scope)
        Decode the given statement into a ParameterNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null. A parameter node is essentially a variable declaration, but in the context of a method declaration.

        Example inputs include:
        • String name
        • int age
        • TreeNode parent
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a ParameterNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        scope - Whether or not the given statement is the beginning of a scope.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ParameterNode.
